 height=\"192\" /></p>\n<p>3. Then click the deactivate button. It will then remove your sites from our license server.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-5408\" src=\"http://help.codexpert.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/deactivate.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1156\" height=\"257\" srcset=\"https://help.codexpert.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/deactivate.png 1156w, https://help.codexpert.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/deactivate-300x67.png 300w, https://help.codexpert.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/deactivate-1024x228.png 1024w, https://help.codexpert.io/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/deactivate-768x171.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1156px) 100vw, 1156px\" /></p>\n<p>That&#8217;s it! As soon as the domains are removed from the license we will process the refund.</p>\n\";s:9:\"protected\";b:0;}s:7:\"excerpt\";a:2:{s:8:\"rendered\";s:330:\"<p>If you face any major issue with Woolementor and want to request for a refund, then you will need to deactivate the license key from the settings. Simply follow the steps below- Head over to Woolementor tab on your WordPress dashboard 2. Click the license tab in settings 3. Then click the deactivate button. It [&hellip;]</p>\n\";s:9:\"protected\";b:0;}s:6:\"author\";i:346;s:14:\"featured_media\";i:0;s:6:\"parent\";i:1960;s:14:\"comment_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:11:\"ping_status\";s:6:\"closed\";s:8:\"template\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"meta\";a:0:{}s:12:\"doc_category\";a:1:{i:0;i:64;}s:7:\"doc_tag\";a:0:{}s:6:\"_links\";a:10:{s:4:\"self\";a:1:{i:0;a:1:{s:4:\"href\";s:49:\"https://help.codexpert.io/wp-json/wp/v2/docs/5404\";}}s:10:\"collection\";a:1:{i:0;a:1:{s:4:\"href\";s:44:\"https://help.codexpert.io/wp-json/wp/v2/docs\";}}s:5:\"about\";a:1:{i:0;a:1:{s:4:\"href\";s:50:\"https://help.codexpert.io/wp-json/wp/v2/types/docs\";}}s:6:\"author\";a:1:{i:0;a:2:{s:10:\"embeddable\";b:1;s:4:\"href\";s:49:\"https://help.codexpert.io/wp-json/wp/v2/users/346\";}}s:7:\"replies\";a:1:{i:0;a:2:{s:10:\"embeddable\";b:1;s:4:\"href\";